Description: Global push-to-hold voice input for Linux/Wayland
 Hold right-Ctrl, speak, release: the recognised text is pasted into
 the currently-focused input field. Backed by Doubao's streaming ASR.
 .
 This package installs the Python application, a systemd --user service
 for auto-start, and a postinst hook that adds the installing user to
 the 'input' group so it can read /dev/input/event* and write
 /dev/uinput without sudo.